40
Credit Rating
As the President explained, during the war revenues will be lower than expenses. In this case new debt is required. This is issued automatically. Debt increases interest costs and will hurt your credit rating. If it drops below B, the Congress will no longer allow recruitment of new units or construction of new ships or buildings.

