41
Credit Rating
To improve your credit rating, you can use certain policies and acts, which will be explained to you shortly, or you may increase taxes or reduce government spending (subsidies) using the sliders. Subsidies and taxes are also linked to policies. Some policies will allow higher taxes and new tax types.\nRemember, high taxes mean less wealth for the private corporations and citizens. High wealth will increase national morale, and vice versa.

