45
Trade
In this panel you see how the supply, demand, and price of each product in the game develops, including over time. Clicking on any product name (line) will open further information on the left. Import and export of selected product is shown in the bottom left.\nIn short, if demand is high and supply is low, prices will increase. If prices are very high, wealth will suffer, reducing national morale.\nIn the graph you will also see information about enemy trade situation. For example, if you blockade rebel ports, the long term effects may be seen in the prices. Again, if the economy cannot be sustained, new debt is required, which increases interest costs, reduces credit rating, and eventually may lead into inability to sustain the war effort.

