107
Supplies
Armies and depots connect to "Important Infrastructure Points" (IIPs). All goods, including military supplies, of your nation flow through these points, depending on supply & demand. The speed is determined by transport capacity.\nAs Springfield, MO, is not connected to a railroad, its transport capacity is quite low. This means moving supplies through it is slow. For example, if it had a railroad connection, capacity would be much higher.\nEspecially larger armies can only be supported when they have good lines of supplies available: rivers, railroad lines, canals, and harbors offer best capacity.

