Order Delays
When an order is given to an army, or a corps, it will be carried out only after a delay (when order delays are enabled in game options). The higher the readiness, the lower the delay. If the unit has telegraph connection, the delay is much lower as well. The delay is shown in the unit panel as a timer, as well as on the map next to the NATO symbol.\nNow, click play, to see how the order delay counts down and the unit moves out.
